    </headerImage>
    <introText>
      <Value><![CDATA[{
  "blocks": {
    "contentData": [],
    "settingsData": [],
    "expose": [],
    "Layout": {}
  },
  "markup": "\u003Cp\u003EContent teams spend a lot of time on repetitive tasks. Umbraco.AI helps by bringing AI assistance directly into the Umbraco backoffice, so editors can work faster without leaving the CMS.\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ch2\u003EWhat Umbraco.AI includes\u003C/h2\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAI-powered text generation\u003C/strong\u003E \u2014 generate and rewrite content directly in the editor.\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMultiple AI providers\u003C/strong\u003E \u2014 connect to Anthropic, OpenAI, or other compatible providers.\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EProfile-based configuration\u003C/strong\u003E \u2014 set up different AI profiles for different use cases across your site.\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EExtensible by design\u003C/strong\u003E \u2014 developers can build custom AI-powered features on top of the Umbraco.AI API.\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n\u003Ch2\u003EWhy teams use it\u003C/h2\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003EUmbraco.AI is used by development teams and content editors who want to bring AI into their Umbraco workflow without building custom integrations from scratch. It is maintained by Umbraco HQ and integrates naturally with the backoffice.\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003ETeams report that it saves time on content-related tasks and makes it easier to experiment with AI-assisted workflows. The package is actively maintained and supports the latest Umbraco LTS releases.\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ch2\u003EFrequently asked questions\u003C/h2\u003E\n\u003Ch3\u003EDo I need my own AI provider account?\u003C/h3\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003EYes. Umbraco.AI connects to your existing AI provider account (Anthropic or OpenAI). You will need an API key from your chosen provider. Costs depend on your provider\u2019s pricing and how frequently your team uses the AI features.\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ch3\u003EWhich versions of Umbraco are supported?\u003C/h3\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003EUmbraco.AI supports Umbraco 13 and above, including the current LTS releases. Check the GitHub repository for the latest compatibility information.\u003C/p\u003E"
}]]></Value>
    </introText>
    <metaDescription>
      <Value><![CDATA[Umbraco.AI adds AI-powered content assistance to the Umbraco backoffice. Connect to Anthropic or OpenAI and start using AI in your content workflow.]]></Value>
    </metaDescription>
